n emphasis on the regeneration of the individual, she soon showed an appreciation of the importance of social conditions. This book challenges all previous interpretations of Lowell as a "genteel" reformer mostly interested in social control of the underclass. Rather, her aim was to cure pauperism, and her strategies eventually led her to support higher wages and full employment.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aArmoede. 0aBiographie. 0aLiefdadigheid. 0aSociale hervormingen. 0aSoziale Probleme, Sozialdienste, Versicherungen. 0aWomen philanthropists. 0aWomen social reformers. 4aCharity Organization Society of the City of New York -- History. 4aHISTORY / United States / General. 4aLowell, Josephine Shaw, 1843-1905. 4aWomen philanthropists -- New York (State) -- Biography. 4aWomen social reformers -- New York (State) -- Biography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Women.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Art & Architecture eBook Packagez9783110353471oZDB-23-HAA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Complete eBook Packagez9783110353488oZDB-23-HCO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z97831104422120 cprintz978067443749440uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.978067443748740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674437487423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674437487/original  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999c1893d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-HAA  aZDB-23-HCO